2. Consider a distributed banking application that is required to be available 24/7/365. What property must be sacrificed under this assumption and why?
----------------------------
In a banking system that has to be working all the time the system can not always have the up to date information. The CAP theorem says that if 
the network is not working right the system can either have the most up to date information or be available but it can not do both.
So, since the banking system has to be available, it might give us information that's a little old or inconsistent when something goes wrong with 
the banking system.
