3. Explain what is Eventual Consistency. Give an example of an application for which eventual consistency is acceptable.
----------------------------
Eventual consistency is a model where changes are not seen by all nodes right away. Over time all replications will be the same on all systems as long as 
no new changes are made. This means that temporary inconsistencies are allowed for a while.
For example Instagram is, like this. When we upload a post it might not show up for all our friends right away, but after a few minutes everyone will be 
able to see it.
