4. What is the best speedup that can be achieved for a program for which 25% of its execution is parallelizable when it runs on a machine with 3 processors? 
Can this speedup be achieved in practice? Explain your answer.
----------------------------
According to Amdahl’s LawNow what we can hope for is about 1.2 times increase in speedup. This is if we have 25 percent of our code to be run at the same 
time and we have 3 processors working together. However, in real life we do not usually achieve this much faster speed. This is because there are a lot of 
factors that slow us down like communicating between systems making sure everything is working together and dealing with uneven workloads. All these factors 
reduce the performance gains.
